text: Sorry for many posts...

<@U1M9R3C8Z> The chaincode is failing to build. See these errors in your Docker logs: ```---> Running in 67eac64ac4e1
src/build-chaincode/utils/utils.go:5:2: cannot find package "<http://github.com/hyperledger/fabric/core/chaincode/shim|github.com/hyperledger/fabric/core/chaincode/shim>" in any of:
    /opt/go/src/github.com/hyperledger/fabric/core/chaincode/shim (from $GOROOT)
    /opt/gopath/src/github.com/hyperledger/fabric/core/chaincode/shim (from $GOPATH)```
That error is caused because you do not have the Hyperledger Fabric source in a `vendor` folder next to your chaincode.
Did you follow the `npm run installgo` step in the Prerequisites section? <https://github.com/IBM-Blockchain/fabric-boilerplate>
